124. A foreigner who meets the following conditions is part of the category of spouse or common-law partner in Canada:
(a) he is the spouse or common-law partner of a guarantor and lives with that guarantor in Canada;
(b) he holds temporary resident status in Canada;
c) a sponsorship application has been filed in his regard.
Did the Officer breach principles of procedural fairness by not disclosing the poison pen letter?
